sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User/SDK
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Operator as Training Operator<br/>Watch API TLS1.2+
    participant Registry as Container Registry<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Master as Master Pod<br/>23456/TCP
    participant Worker1 as Worker Pod 1<br/>23456/TCP
    participant Worker2 as Worker Pod 2<br/>23456/TCP
    participant Prometheus as Prometheus<br/>8080/TCP HTTP

    Note over User,Worker2: Flow 1: Training Job Submission (PyTorchJob)

    User->>K8sAPI: POST /apis/kubeflow.org/v1/namespaces/{ns}/pytorchjobs<br/>Auth: User credentials (HTTPS/TLS1.2+)
    K8sAPI->>Operator: Watch Event: PyTorchJob Created<br/>ServiceAccount Token (TLS1.2+)
    Operator->>K8sAPI: GET PyTorchJob spec<br/>ServiceAccount Token (HTTPS/443)
    Operator->>K8sAPI: CREATE Pod (master)<br/>ServiceAccount Token (HTTPS/443)
    Operator->>K8sAPI: CREATE Pod (worker-1)<br/>ServiceAccount Token (HTTPS/443)
    Operator->>K8sAPI: CREATE Pod (worker-2)<br/>ServiceAccount Token (HTTPS/443)
    Operator->>K8sAPI: CREATE Service (headless)<br/>ServiceAccount Token (HTTPS/443)
    Operator->>K8sAPI: CREATE ConfigMap (training config)<br/>ServiceAccount Token (HTTPS/443)
    K8sAPI->>Registry: Pull container image<br/>Pull Secrets (HTTPS/443)
    Registry-->>K8sAPI: Container image
    K8sAPI-->>Master: Pod created
    K8sAPI-->>Worker1: Pod created
    K8sAPI-->>Worker2: Pod created

    Note over Master,Worker2: Flow 2: Distributed Training Execution

    Master->>Worker1: Initialize rendezvous<br/>TCP/23456 (plaintext)
    Master->>Worker2: Initialize rendezvous<br/>TCP/23456 (plaintext)
    Worker1->>Master: Synchronize gradients<br/>TCP/23456 (plaintext)
    Worker2->>Master: Synchronize gradients<br/>TCP/23456 (plaintext)
    Master->>Worker1: Broadcast model updates<br/>TCP/23456 (plaintext)
    Master->>Worker2: Broadcast model updates<br/>TCP/23456 (plaintext)

    Note over Master,Worker2: Training iterations continue...

    Master->>K8sAPI: Update PyTorchJob status (Succeeded)<br/>ServiceAccount Token (HTTPS/443)
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Watch Event: Job Succeeded<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: CREATE Event (JobSucceeded)<br/>ServiceAccount Token (HTTPS/443)

    Note over Prometheus,Operator: Flow 3: Metrics Collection

    Prometheus->>Operator: GET /metrics<br/>HTTP/8080 (plaintext)
    Operator-->>Prometheus: Prometheus metrics (job counts, reconciliation duration)
